{
  "texts": [
    "This problem introduced the need for positional encoding.",
    "Positional information helps the LLM to learn relationships among tokens based on both their absolute and relative positions in a sequence.",
    "There are dozens of methods to encode token positions.",
    "The original transformer model used predefined sinusoidal functions of different frequencies to encode the position of each token in the sequence (Vaswani et al. 2017).",
    "In contrast, GPT-3 learned how to add position encoding to tokens by adapting the parameters of its network during training to identify an approach for positional encoding that is consistent with the objective function of the model (Brown et al. 2020)."
  ]
}